    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document defines a protocol for exchanging DNS queries (OPCODE 0) over the Constrained Application Protocol (CoAP).  These CoAP messages can be protected by (D)TLS-Secured CoAP or Object Security for Constrained RESTful Environments (OSCORE) to provide encrypted DNS message exchange for constrained devices in the Internet of Things (IoT).&lt;/p&gt;</t>
